node.text:
My knees tend to get very tight whether I’m training a lot or resting .  I do blame long femurs 🤪 I give people a jealous look that show up and just start squatting 😂 Frederik is one of those. Although I don’t think you should, you should always prep a little 😉

Wanted to share with you one of the ways I like loosening them up.  Scraping has been a part of me prep and recovery since I hurt my back in 2013

@sidekicktool in my bag at all times 👌

#scraping #recovery #prep #ad #sidekick

Mix all ingredients and put in freezer - stir frequently to avoid crystallization. 

My favorite snack!

node.text:
Today’s Monday challenge is a little different from what we are used to!

Today we are going to slow things down, take time to wind down and get CENTERED. Today, everything moves so fast and we very rarely find time to slow things down, and let our mind and soul take a breather. I have been using this breathing technique on and off for many years and it’s a great way to re-center yourself. Give it a go and let me know how it feels.

The protocol is as follows: 

20 to 30 deep breaths
Hold your breath on the Exhale
Once you cannot hold anymore take one deep breath in and hold.
Go directly into the next cycle of 20 to 30 deep breath and repeat for three cycles. 

#mondaychallenge #breathing #mentalgame #slowdown #meditate #oxygen #co2 #wimhof #enjoythejourney

node.text:
Today, I failed. 

Social media often acts as a highlight reel showing the best of peoples lives. Their biggest lifts, their fastest runs, the tidiest homes, perfectly folded laundry and always having things under control. 

If social media is a true representation of how people live their lives on a day to day basis, I need to seriously reevaluate mine.

we have always been taught to keep up a front, pretend like everything is under control even when it’s not. No matter who you are, you cannot always be in control of what happens around you. We have many obligations daily, work, taking care of our family, taking care of ourselves And many other responsibilities that comes along with being a grown-up. 

I have found that the best way to navigate this confusing landscape, is to just look at the obstacle right in front of me. It is easy to get overwhelmed looking at all the obstacles the lie on the road ahead, constantly thinking of how you’re going to tackle each of them, and often postponing it just to give your head a little bit of a break. 

Today I failed at doing this. And I will fail many more times. But I will always get back up, put my head down and get to work. Always remember, everyone has their struggles, and the knowledge that you are not alone is to me one of the most comforting things when I feel overwhelmed.
#real #vulnerable #control #highlights #focus #family #live #love #laugh #together

node.text:
“Eat your greens kiddo..”
 same goes for you behind the screen  buddy..!”

Knowledge is power @rpstrength.

There are very few things in my life that I would change, but if I had to mention one thing that I wish I would’ve done differently, it would be my relationship to food growing up. I did gymnastics when I was a kid and “simply didn’t have time to eat” and it often left me with very little energy during training and competition, and I was one of the smallest ones in my  school class until I stopped gymnastics. 

There was very little focus from my coaches on what to eat to fuel performance and a stronger focus on just staying light lean and small. I firmly believe that I would’ve been a better gymnast if I would’ve fueled for that purpose and gotten guidance any on what to eat and how much. In my opinion nutrition should be a class in elementary school, give everyone a chance to make informed decisions, know what the food does for you and how you can make mealtime enjoyable and keep you healthy. 

Whether you want to fuel for performance or for looks it is important to keep track of what are you eat to be able to make the small adjustments needed to configure the diet to exactly what you need it to do for you. If you find the right balance it’s no longer a diet it’s just how you support the way you choose to live your life. @rpstrength Takes all the guesswork out of eating and make sure you can focus on what really matters.

node.text:
logging miles and water with @nuunhydration. Great for performance and for flavor. 

Here is a fun “test”: 

1: step on the scale pre run (no clothes)
2: RUN
3: step on the scale post run (no clothes)

If you drink during, note down exactly how much 

Here is how mine went today:

70,3kg pre run
Run: 4 sets 4x400m at 5k pace, 30sec rest between 400s, rest 5min between sets. 
69,4kg post run

No water during

Did I burn off 900g of fat? Well not quite. Most of what was lost is water

Why does this matter?

When your body becomes low on electrolytes (dehydrated and high secretion of electrolytes with the sweat), it can impair your body's functions, such as blood clotting, muscle contractions, acid balance, and fluid regulation. Your heart is a muscle, so that means electrolytes help regulate your heartbeat. 

Long story short… DRINK YOUR WATER AND REPLENISH YOUR ELECTROLYTES. 

#ad #nuun #fuel #hydration #science #running #fitness #sweat #enjoythejourney #lovewhatyoudo
